📽 @outdoorkindaguy

There's just something about a quokka that makes everything better 😀❤️ Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on planetfervor.com (link in my bio: @planetfervor)

Rottnest Island is known worldwide to be the home of the happiest animal on earth - The Quokka. Close relatives of wallabies, these animals are found all over Rottnest Island in Australia. 🙂🇦🇺

node.text:
The biggest animal on Earth via @adam_ernster. 🐋 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @planetfervor

Blue Whales can hold their breath for about 90 minutes, reaching a maximum length of 100 feet or 30 metres long and weight up to 200 tons, it is the largest animal known to have ever existed... 🤯

This video was taken in the Santa Barbara Channel where over 27 different types of whales and dolphins call this place home, making these waters one of the best whale watching areas in the world.

From May to September you can see Blue Whales, Minke Whales and Humpback Whales. Occasionally, you can see Right Whales or Orcas. All season long you have an excellent chance of seeing dolphins, porpoises, seals and sea lions.

Who would you share this experience with? 🐳

📽 @condorexpresssb & @adam_ernster
📍 Santa Barbara, California, USA
🎶 Thomas Newman - Wow

Have you ever seen @nature hummocks? 🤩 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @planetfervor

The wonderland of Puga Valley in Ladakh, India via @apytravelstories will left you speechless 🤯 If you are a @nature lover, then you should really visit this place. It's incredible landscape attracts the visitors.

The Puga valley in the Changthang valley lies at about 22 km to the east of the Salt Lake valley across the Polokonka La pass (5,350 m). It is famous for its borax and sulphur deposits and hot water springs.

📽 @apytravelstories
📍 Puga Valley, Ladakh, India
🎶 Kathleen - Pure Imagination
